Makes sense - which do we prefer:
```python
if not verbose:
    return return Http(strict=True)

headers = False if verbose == 'body' else True
body = False if verbose == 'headers' else True
return VerboseHttp(…)
```
or
```python
if verbose:
    headers = False if verbose == 'body' else True
    body = False if verbose == 'headers' else True
    return VerboseHttp(…)
else:
    return return Http(strict=True)
```

The second `border-spacing` value should be used here because it contains the horizontal size ([ref](https://developer.mozilla.org/en-US/docs/Web/CSS/border-spacing))

```css
/* border-spacing: horizontal vertical */
border-spacing: 1cm 2em;
```

